node.text:
Here is a video I filmed before becoming pregnant last year with Exercise Physiologist @jono.freeman. We go through some tests & exercises to do to help achieve maximal activation of the glutes when training. This might help people who are “quad dominant” and have trouble feeling their glutes firing in movements like the squat, glute bridge, hip thrust, lunge, deadlift, steps ups.  These tests & exercises helped me HEAPS to not only activate my glutes properly but to grow & strengthen them. .
#gluteactivation #gluterecruitment #glutestrengthening #glutebuilding #emilyskye #jonofreeman

Everyone is different and we all have different squat positions so it’s important to find the correct position for you! .
Also, my new @youcanbyemilyskye podcast episode is out with the person who “fixes” my body when it’s broken! Exercise Physiologist @jono.freeman 😃 We talk about how to activate the glutes properly so you can strengthen them, become more anatomically “balanced” & grow your booty! 
My podcast is available on apple podcasts & on Spotify - just search “You Can by Emily Skye” or go to the weblink in my @youcanbyemilyskye profile!
Don’t forgot to leave me feedback by rating & reviewing & let me know what else you’d like me to cover in an upcoming episode! ☺️👍🏼 I hope you like it! .
.

.
(Air squats, banded squats & goblet squats)
.
💕 Aa always I’m drinking my fav @womensbest BCAA AMINOS 😋
. •	Find the right stance that’s right for YOU - don’t just copy how someone else squats. •	Keep an engaged core and straight back •	Align your head with your spine •	Push out with your knees (don’t let them come “in”) •	Don’t worry if your knees track slightly over your toes - at some point this has to happen especially if you have long femurs (like me). If I tried to stop them passing my toes I’d actually fall back and wouldn’t be able to squat very low.
.
.

node.text:
It’s one of the most common incorrectly performed exercises I see - so hopefully this tutorial helps. ☺️
The glute kickback is not an exercise I do often as I don’t believe it is the best way to grow or strengthen the glutes simply because you can’t lift enough weight to cause the most amount of muscle fibre recruitment possible. When you use heavy weights for the kickback it ends up putting pressure on the lower back therefore I think it’s definitely a bonus exercise you can add into your glute day (providing you have good technique) but don’t expect much glute growth if it’s the only exercise you’re relying on “to grow your butt”. In my opinion nothing beats hip thrusts, lunges, deadlifts, squats, step ups, bridges, & split squats etc. for glute building & strengthening!! 🍑👊🏼
.
.
#glutekickback #kickback #glutebuilding #buildyourglutes #exercisetutorial #emilyskye #glutekickbacktutorial

node.text: Chat about not letting your fears of judgement and criticism from others hold you back. Be yourself and do what you want to do in life! ☺️👊🏼

🏃🏻‍♀️ I used to get teased at school for looking so funny while running. 🤣🙈⁣
⁣
None of this is easy BUT at least it can be fun! I spend most of our sprint sessions laughing at myself! 🤣 ⁣
The only way to improve is to do MORE of it. 😉⁣
Feeling so grateful for my body, and for great training sessions with awesome people. 🙌🏼 I ALWAYS feel better after training! 🥰⁣
⁣
By the way, isn’t @freezma such a WEAPON! 💪🏼 My goal is to get CLOSE to catching him one day. 🤣 I can only dream. 😜⁣
⁣
⁣
#explosivetraining #sprints #sprinttraining #plyometrictraining #plyometrics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emily Skye on July 16, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and activewear.

node.text:
#FlexFriday 💪🏼😉 I got back into sprints today (& some hand stands 😜)! I haven’t been able to make it lately, we’ve been flat out with moving house, kids & work. Being fit & healthy is a lifestyle for me but I don’t always get to train & that’s ok! I just try to do the best I can & that’s good enough!! ☺️
I always feel so much better after training though! 🙌🏼
So keen to work on my explosive strength right now! What’s your fitness goal at the moment?

🎉 I can’t believe it! 😱 I have my own line of supplements in collaboration with @womensbest 😃 - THEY’RE AVAILABLE NOW!! 🙌🏼⁣
⁣
My supplement line includes:⁣
⁣
Vegan Protein in Salted Caramel flavour 😋 - This protein is the only one my gut can tolerate & doesn’t make me bloated & crampy! 🙌🏼⁣
⁣
BCAA in Coconut Mango flavour 🥥🥭 - The best flavoured BCAAs ever!! ⁣
⁣
Smart Bar in Chocolate Almond Coconut flavour 🍫🥥 - They’re protein bars that taste just like chocolate bars! Not even kidding! 🤤⁣
⁣
	⁃	My smart bars are EXCLUSIVELY available at the 2291 GNC stores across the USA! 🙌🏼 They also sell online with same day delivery to USA customers (for orders placed before 1pm) ☺️⁣
⁣
⁣
I’ve personally chosen each of these supplements to have in my line & the flavours I chose are all my most favourite flavours ever! 🤤 I’m so excited for you to try them! 😃🙌🏼⁣
⁣
⁣
#womensbest #athleteseries #emilyskye

🎉 EXCITING NEWS +  GIVEAWAY!! 🎉⁣
🔊 The giveaway is now closed & the 3 winners have been contacted. Thank you to everyone for participating & for your support!! 🙏🏼😘
⁣
I’m so excited to reveal what I’ve been working on! 😃 I’m launching my own supplement line with @womensbest! 💃🏼 It launches on the 13th July at 2am AEST!!⁣
⁣
My supplement line will include:⁣
⁣
Vegan Protein in Salted Caramel flavour 😋⁣
⁣
BCAA Amino in Coconut Mango flavour 🥥🥭⁣
⁣
Smart Bar in Chocolate Almond Coconut flavour 🍫🥥⁣
⁣
I’ve personally picked these supplements & flavours & they’re absolutely delicious! I can’t wait for you to try them!! 🤤⁣
⁣
⁣
 ✨ GIVEAWAY DETAILS✨⁣
⁣
- To celebrate the launch, we’re doing a giveaway!! 3 winners will win my whole supplement line + a Women’s Best outfit of your choice! ⁣
⁣
💖 TO ENTER:⁣
⁣
1. Follow me - @emilyskyefit & @womensbest⁣
⁣
2. Like this post⁣
⁣
3. Tag a friend - you can enter as many times as you like by tagging more friends. ☺️⁣
⁣
⁣
💕 GOOD LUCK! 🤗⁣
⁣
- There will also be exciting news for everyone in the USA regarding the Smart Bars too so stay tuned. 🥰

node.text:
Nailed it! 🤪 👉🏼 Scroll across for my attempt at trying to get nice pic of my babies & me. 😁 I actually wouldn’t change a thing though! I love that the shots are just natural & fun. ⁣
⁣
We’re in the middle of packing to move houses so it’s hectic here at the moment! 😆 I’m a little sad to move because we have so many memories here & Izaac was born on the lounge room floor. 😢 We’ll make more memories in our new house though. 🥰

node.text:
I shot something really exciting for @womensbest yesterday which is one of the reasons I’ve been training SO hard the past 9 months to get fit again - can’t wait to share what it is with you! 🙌🏼😃⁣⁣
Health & fitness changed my life & I love living this lifestyle & wouldn’t ever want to stop. Getting fit & healthy again after having my 2nd baby Izaac was important to me, not because I don’t like my body when I’m not fit, I love it through all stages.. but because I love who I am when I’m fit; I’m happier, more motivated, have a clearer mind, have more energy, AND I love the way I look when I’m fit & strong… there seems to be this belief that wanting to look good is a negative thing. I do not agree with sacrificing your health in order to look a certain way (whether that’s mental or physical) BUT there’s absolutely nothing with wanting to look your best. 😉⁣
⁣
#1yearpostpartum

node.text:
🎉 My baby boy turned ONE yesterday!! 😮🥺 (so hard to get a pic with kids 🙈)⁣
I can’t believe it’s been a whole year since I accidentally gave birth to Zaccy on the floor at home! 🤣 Poor @recdedmond had to hold his head to stop him birthing too fast so he didn’t end up on the floor! 🙈🤣 ⁣
His birth was super fast fast & everything else he does is fast too! Should’ve called him Speedy Gonzales (which was actually my nickname at school haha).⁣
⁣
I’ve really been feeling alllll the emotions lately. 😭 Seeing my kids grow up is the BEST but also makes me sad. They’ll always be my babies though right?! 🥺⁣
⁣
👉🏼 Scroll across for some cute newborn pics of my little man. 😍🥰⁣
⁣
⁣
#oneyearold #babyboyis1 #birthdayboy

node.text:
#11monthspostpartum⁣
It’s taken me nearly a year after having Izaac to get fit again. I knew I’d do it though. I feel fantastic & I’m so proud of myself. 🥰⁣
Scroll across to see some of the snippets of my 2nd postnatal fitness journey. 👉🏼 ⁣
⁣
I STRUGGLED A LOT! IT HAS BEEN HAAAARD WORK. ⁣
⁣
Sometimes your body doesn’t seem to be representing your hard work and commitment & you feel like you’re not getting anywhere.⁣
There was a whole month or so where I felt like I wasn’t changing at all. It was frustrating but I knew I just had to keep going & keep working hard. I always get myself uncomfortable when I train. (If you’ve ever seen me at the gym, I’m the maniac who looks like they’re about to pass out). 🤣 ⁣
⁣
I also had to be more strict with my food than I’ve ever been. I make sure I get enough fuel & nutrients but it really does come down to being in calorie deficit. Can’t argue with the science!⁣
⁣
The thing with consistency is that after a while results start to show in many ways - your fitness, the way you feel & the way you look.⁣
⁣
If you want to feel fit & strong- you CAN do it! Don’t doubt yourself! It just takes hard work, commitment & consistency. I believe in you just as I believe in myself. ☺️⁣
⁣
You’ve got this!! 👊🏼⁣
⁣
Also, I want to thank all of you who have been so supportive of me throughout my whole journey, especially my postnatal journey. Being a parent is tough, getting fitter is tough BUT YOU’RE TOUGHER!!💪🏼 - Had to add that haha! 😜 It’s true though. 😘⁣

node.text:
Us Aussies be like: Temp drops below 20°C / 68°F - beanies & uggies come out & fires go on! 🤣🙈 (or maybe that’s just me?! 🤷🏻‍♀️)

Do you prefer hot or cold climate? 🥵🥶

node.text:
👶🏼 Mummy’s boy forever I hope! 🥰😍
He’s on the move now! 🏃🏼 Scroll across 👉🏼 
Can you believe he’s 1 in a few weeks!! 😱

HOW TO SQUAT⁣
⁣
Wearing: @womensbestwear⁣
⁣
• Find the right stance that’s right for YOU. Every body is different so our squat setup is going to be a bit different to one another. - I have a tutorial on how to find the squat set-up that’s right for you in my IGTV tab.⁣
Personally, I’m much more comfortable & functional with my squats when my feet are positioned fairly wide apart with my toes slightly pointed out.⁣
⁣
⁣
• Roll shoulders back & down (with chest “out”)⁣
⁣
• Keep an engaged core and straight back ⁣
⁣
• For a standard squat try to be as upright as possible with your torso (without leaning too far forward)⁣
⁣
• Try to align your head with your spine ⁣
⁣
• Push out with your knees (don’t let them cave “in”) ⁣
⁣
• Try to push through your glutes during the concentric phase of the squat (up phase)⁣
⁣
• Just squat as low as you can comfortably go without losing form.⁣
⁣
• Don’t worry if your knees track slightly over your toes - at some point this has to happen especially if you have long femurs (like me). If I tried to stop them passing my toes I’d actually fall back and wouldn’t be able to squat very low. ☺️⁣
⁣
• Master your technique before adding weight or upping the weight.⁣
⁣
⁣
🦶🏼 I love squatting barefoot, it’s really helped strengthen my feet. ☺️⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
